Description:
The High Life
Built to last, this solidly constructed home offers an uncompromising lifestyle on top of the hill, with picturesque views of Brimbank Park. Boasting a unique split-level design offering a versatile floorplan for even the largest of families. Accommodation includes: 5 bedrooms, master with en suite and walk in robe, study, multiple formal and informal living zones including formal lounge and dining, open plan kitchen and meals area, plus a rumpus room with fireplace. Outdoors offers beautifully landscaped front and rear gardens with beautifully shaded entertaining space and a remote double garage with internal access. With the added comfort of ducted heating, evaporative cooling, alarm system, vacuum maid and more. A rare opportunity to enter a tightly held suburb enjoying all the best that Keilor Village has to offer. Call today to book your private inspection!

Description:
Light and Style with a Perfect Poolside Surprise!
Beyond the wide front garden and classic Colonial-inspired facade, this single-level family home delivers a truly twenty-first century lifestyle thanks to its contemporary tones, quality enhancements throughout and terrific poolside entertaining area. Well-proportioned rooms and an abundance of natural light, the home's immaculate interior comprises a central hallway accessing three spacious bedrooms (all with built-in robes) and stylish modern bathroom, open lounge/dining area leading through to the kitchen/meals complete with dishwasher and stainless steel cooking appliances. Other features include ducted heating and split-system a/c, open fireplace (lounge), solid hardwood floors, laundry and separate WC. Step outside to discover a substantial backyard garden with undercover patio/entertaining area and inviting solar-heated pool with paved surrounds, plus a garage/workshop via gated driveway. Situated in a popular and convenient Keilor neighbourhood, it's close to village shops and eateries, expansive parkland and riverside trails, as well as Overnewton College, public transport and easy freeway access. Land approx. 631sqm.

Description:
Magnificent Outlook For The Future
Drink in amazing views of tranquil canopies to the backdrop of birdsong: on a generous allotment of approximately 775m2 with sweeping street frontage, this is the perfect spot to bring your dream home to life (subject to council approval). The present three bedroom home demonstrates superb views upstairs from just about every direction, but there is so much more you could do on the site to create a stylish haven for everyone in the family. The serene position, where Horseshoe Bend Road curves into Garden Avenue, is opposite parkland by the banks of the Maribyrnong River, close to Keilor Village, Keilor Primary and transport, a quick walk to the trails and relaxing open spaces of Brimbank Park and a short drive to excellent schools including Overnewton College and Penleigh & Essendon Grammar. When it comes to city commutes it's easy to access the Calder Freeway and Ring Road, making it entirely possible to reach the heart of the city in very little time.

Description:
Single Level Oasis In The Village
One of the best you'll see, this immaculate, beautifully renovated three bedroom single level residence boasts secluded garden setting, resort style outdoor entertaining options and private street facing aspect in a cul-de-sac. A short walk from the heart of Keilor Village, the home is secluded behind high fences where generous front and rear courtyards offer privacy. Low maintenance surrounds are highlighted by Balinese-inspired alfresco deck featuring relaxing swim spa and covered entertainment area. Inside is just as impressive with a bright living zone, featuring freestanding wood burner, and spacious open plan dining and kitchen spaces flaunting stone benches, modern cabinetry and quality stainless steel appliances. There are three delightful bedrooms, including two presenting either walk-in or built-in-robe. They are elegantly served by modern main bathroom, laundry area and separate toilet. Split-system air conditioning, ceiling fans, skylight, automated roller shutters, modern floor coverings, storage and remote controlled carport complete this quality package. Enviably placed to shops, cafe's, schools, buses and parklands.

Description:
Executive Living At Its Finest
Witness perfection at every turn with this astutely renovated four bedroom, three bathroom executive residence showcasing exceptional indoor/outdoor living and entertaining opportunities. Serenely located, an impeccably presented layout it comprises double-door entry, open study and formal living/dining zones highlighted by Archer gas-log fire, premium flooring and seamless access onto an alfresco deck featuring large retractable awnings and heated swim spa with inbuilt television. Enjoying great connection to the outdoors is an expansive entertainment room featuring high ceilings, overhead projector and a series of sliding double-glazed aspects opening to beautifully landscaped gardens/barbeque zone. A gourmet kitchen displays high end Bosch induction cook top, stainless steel pyrolytic oven, dishwasher, double pantry and stone counters, including servery bar/sliding window. Elegantly served by two luxe ensuites, shower room and laundry are four beautifully appointed bedrooms with either walk-in/built-in-robes. Boasts ducted heating/evaporative cooling, split-system air conditioner, CCTV/alarm, storage, solar electricity, automated double garage and more. Enviably placed near parklands, Keilor Village, Overnewton College, transport and freeways.

Family Luxury In Cul-De-Sac Locale
Close to Keilor Village and Overnewton College, this outstanding three bedroom, two bathroom plus study family home has been meticulously renovated and extended to the highest of construction and design standards. Lined with reclaimed messmate floorboards, extensive living zones include a vast kitchen/meals boasting ample stone topped cabinetry, premium appliances including integrated refrigeration, microwave and dishwasher plus servery window to the alfresco deck. Description:
First Class Resort Living
Cutting edge design and seamless indoor/outdoor flow, this designer approx 40 square family home sets the benchmark in entertaining and quality living. Superbly designed to capture northerly light whilst showcasing uncompromised quality, it features majestic three metre high ceilings and gleaming hardwood floors. The prestigious open plan living and dining zone gracefully connects to the stunning alfresco and solar heated fully tiled pool. Gourmet kitchen generously appointed with an extra-large granite island bench, dual pyrolytic ovens, induction cooktop and walk in pantry. Four spacious bedrooms offer either walk in or built in robes, master serviced by a luxurious fully tiled ensuite. An extensive list of features includes a entertainment room, double glazed windows throughout, lux family bathroom, powder room, ducted heating, refrigerated cooling, stone feature gas fireplace, internal and external ceiling fans, exceptional storage, manicured gardens and remote integrated double garage. The quality continues with the prestigious location, nearby schools include Overnewton and St Augustines Primary and moments to trendy Keilor Village.

Description:
Substantial Serenity On Approximately 696m2
Situated in a prime dress circle location of established stately homes, this inviting three bedroom, two bathroom home comes with all the credentials of convenience - think prestige schools, shops, and freeway access all close by. Generous proportions meet gracious style to ensure this property delivers a relaxed lifestyle, its elevated position even taking in soothing bushland views over parklands and nature trails. A welcoming entry alcove flows freely through bi-folds to the sunken formal lounge with magnificent raked ceilings, dining room, kitchen/meals (appointed with timber cabinetry/ drawers, 900mm ceramic cooktop, Chef oven/grill, walk-in-pantry and dishwasher) and decked alfresco entertaining. Additionally, a huge family room is perfectly positioned to take in the tranquil scenery of Taylors Creek reserve. Excellent accommodation comprises double-sized bedrooms (BIRs), master with walk-through-robes and ensuite, with the central bathroom boasting an opulent corner spa. Includes a double garage, ample off street parking to fit your caravan/boat, 3rd toilet, storage, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, ducted vacuum, external awnings, intercom.

Description:
Poised For Family Enjoyment
Tucked away in a tranquil locale, walking distance to St Augustine's Primary School, Overnewton College, public transport and parks, this four bedroom, two bathroom plus study home is poised for family enjoyment. Spacious lounge and dining areas are serviced by a stylish kitchen boasting granite counters, glass splashbacks, ample storage, 900mm cooking appliances and dual drawer dishwasher. Description:
Private, Pristine And Impressive
Perched high at the rear of a pristine, secluded development, this three bedroom townhouse enjoys tranquillity and extensive vistas to impress starters, families and investors. A spacious interior presents vast living zones on both levels, commencing with a huge L-shaped multipurpose room (wood heater), ideal for any combination of retreat, entertainment, study or additional accommodation. Like the upstairs living area, it too spills to the outdoors. A smart kitchen services free flowing lounge and dining areas, the latter opening to a sunny, elevated alfresco deck. Meanwhile, three well scaled bedrooms include BIRs and share a spotless main bathroom. There's also a remote controlled garage with internal access, security alarm, a full laundry, ducted heating, two split system air conditioning units and good storage options. Further enhanced by close proximity to Keilor Primary School, Keilor Village, Overnewton College and freeways.

Description:
Family Flexibility with Parkland Proximity
Moments from the open spaces of Taylors Creek Linear Park, this pristine single-level home occupies a wonderfully wide allotment providing a family lifestyle of immediate quality and versatility along with terrific scope to modernise and personalise. Immaculate from start to finish, the home's free-flowing interior comprises four generous bedrooms (all with built-in robes) and study/home office, master ensuite and main family bathroom complete with spa bath. Multiple living zones include an elegant formal lounge and adjoining dining area (both with chandeliers), spacious living room and light-filled family/meals area accompanied by a timber-cabinet kitchen with ample cupboard space. Other highlights include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, ducted vacuum, family-sized laundry, plus a wide backyard with established trees and handy storage shed, deep double garage (r/c) and horseshoe driveway with dual crossovers. Endless walking/cycling trails virtually at your doorstep, it also offers close proximity to popular schools including Overnewton College, public transport, local shopping precincts and easy freeway access.
